        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 2:41PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 238 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms over
the greater Cotopaxi/Texas Creek area or 56 miles southwest of
Colorado Springs. This complex of storms was showing little
movement.

HAZARD...Very heavy rain, Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Heavy rain will impact the region. Flash flooding could
occur with these storms and a flash flood warning may be
needed if these storms do not weaken and or remain
stationary for a period time. Small hail a gusty winds to
40 mph will also be possible.

Locations impacted include...
Texas Creek, Howard, Cotopaxi, Coaldale, and Hillside.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
